The paper deals with distributed algorithms for network design problems, specifically the minimum $k$-edge-connected spanning subgraph problem. This falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The algorithms presented in the paper involve graph algorithms and data structures, which are covered in computer science theory (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the problem of finding minimum spanning trees and related problems is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
